---
import DocsLayout from "../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Tool ingestion" description="How tokenuse reads local AI coding tool session files.">
  <p class="docs-eyebrow">TOOL INGESTION</p>
  <h1>Reads local files, not live traffic</h1>
  <p class="docs-lede">
    tokenuse reads usage data directly from local files written by AI coding tools. There is no proxy, no API key,
    no telemetry endpoint, and no live watcher.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Tool</th><th>Source</th><th>Token quality</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Claude Code</td>
        <td><code>~/.claude/projects/</code> and Claude Desktop local agent sessions</td>
        <td>Exact token/cache usage, tool calls, Bash commands, MCP tools</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Codex</td>
        <td><code>~/.codex/sessions/**/rollout-*.jsonl</code></td>
        <td>Exact per-turn token-count deltas, cached input, reasoning output, and tool calls</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Cursor</td>
        <td>Cursor <code>state.vscdb</code></td>
        <td>Exact when <code>tokenCount</code> exists; estimated fallback otherwise</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>GitHub Copilot</td>
        <td><code>~/.copilot/session-state/</code> and VS Code Copilot Chat transcripts</td>
        <td>Legacy output exact when present; transcripts estimated</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Data path</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Each adapter discovers local files for one tool.</li>
    <li>The adapter parses sources into normalized call records.</li>
    <li>A shared dedup set prevents double-counting during one ingestion run.</li>
    <li>The dashboard aggregates the normalized records by period, tool, project, model, commands, and MCP servers.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    The embedded pricing table is LiteLLM-derived. The default build never fetches it at runtime. Model lookup canonicalizes
    model names, resolves known aliases, then falls back when no match exists.
  </p>

  <pre><code>cost = multiplier * (
    input_tokens * input_rate
  + output_tokens * output_rate
  + cache_creation_input_tokens * cache_write_rate
  + cache_read_input_tokens * cache_read_rate
  + web_search_requests * web_search_rate
)</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
